article.description: Reeves Nelson finished with 14 points and 12 rebounds and UCLA used a late 12-2 run to pull away from Oregon State for a 62-52 victory.
article.headline: UCLA puts away Oregon State with late 12-2 run
article.linkText: UCLA polishes off Oregon State with late run
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Reeves Nelson finished with 14 points and 12 rebounds and UCLA used a late 12-2 run to pull away from Oregon State for a 62-52 victory Saturday night. Nikola Dragovic added 13 points and Michael Roll had 11 for the Bruins (10-11, 5-4 Pac-10), who rebounded from Thursday's loss at Oregon. Calvin Haynes had a game-high 16 points for the Beavers (9-12, 3-6), and Roeland Schaftenaar added 11. UCLA led 38-35 before going on a 12-2 run that gave the Bruins a 50-37 lead with 4:57 to play. Oregon State got no closer than six the rest of the way. UCLA ended the first half on an 11-2 run to lead 24-18 at halftime.
